AB  - This paper examines the optimal behavior of a multinational firm's subsidiary in a host country when learning of its production techniques by its native rivals occurs. In a dynamic framework, it is shown, among other things, that (a) it is worthwhile for the subsidiary to import better technology from its parent firm and that (b) such technology transfer may not benefit the firms of the host country despite their learning, while the host country as a whole does benefit.
