AB  - This paper constructs a framework that is suitable for the analysis of a dual exchange market regime characterized by intermarket leakage. The model incorporates the fact that in reality certain proportions of both trade account and service account items are settled in the financial market on account of both legally-sanctioned leakage and fraudulent transactions. The model is utilized to investigate the dynamic and static properties of the economy with respect to the degrees of export, import and service account leakage as well as with respect to other parameters of interest.
